review_blob: Deep rich purple, ruby red on the edges. Sweet blackberryish on the nose. Full palate. Delicious on all fronts.
Smells like bubblegum, palate is almost chewable. Almost too sweet but the other aspects contribute to surprising balance.
I am not going to try and be nerdy on this one... its is damned delicious. An amazing sensation on my palate.

The name says it all. Color, flavor, palate, nose, and medium to full body of a perfectly ripe strawberry... With enough prominent alcohol (on the palate, not the nose) to remind you its not just fruit juice.

Surprised by the lack of grape in the nose, given the 90/10 blend. Not at all a bad thing as leaves palate open without expectation. Very sweet and full bodied, it is like an alcoholic mixed berry compote worthy of the best pancakes or cheesecake.

Nose has slight hints of tannin with obvious oakey tones..
Despite its honey origin, smell resembles a sweet white grape wine. Palate is clean and crisp, not too sweet. The alcohol and oakeyness cut through the honey creating a very pleasant and palateble balance.
